@startuml Product Lifecycle â€” User Level
title Product Lifecycle (Create, Edit, View, Delete)

actor "User" as user
participant "Products Page" as list
participant "Create Dialog" as create
participant "Product Detail" as detail

== Create Product ==

user -> list : Navigates to /products
user -> list : Clicks "Add Product"
list -> create : Modal/dialog opens

user -> create : Enters product name
user -> create : Clicks "Create"
create -> list : Product appears in list

== View Product Detail ==

user -> list : Clicks on product card
list -> detail : Opens /products/:id

user -> detail : Sees 5 tabs:\n- Overview\n- Obligations\n- Technical File\n- Risk Findings\n- Dependencies
note right of detail : Overview shows product info,\nrepo status, SBOM status,\nvuln summary, and compliance score.

== Edit Product ==

user -> detail : Clicks "Edit" button in header
detail -> detail : Header switches to inline\nedit form (name, description,\nversion, CRA category, etc.)
user -> detail : Changes product name
user -> detail : Clicks "Save"
detail -> detail : Edit mode closes,\nupdated name displays

== Delete Product ==

user -> detail : Clicks "Delete" button
detail -> detail : Confirmation dialog appears
user -> detail : Confirms deletion
detail -> list : Redirects to /products\nProduct no longer in list

@enduml
